## 📖 About this Notice

This file outlines the principles for use, attribution, and collaboration  
within the `KIMU` documentation and conceptual materials.  
It is meant to support a culture of openness, clarity, and creative respect.


---


## 📦 Usage and Distribution

All non-executable content in this repository  
(including documentation, naming conventions, design structures, and conceptual texts)  
is freely reusable, remixable, and shareable — even for commercial purposes —  
as long as appropriate credit is given to the original author.

Please retain this `NOTICE` file in any redistributed or derived version of the content,  
in accordance with the terms of the [CC BY 4.0](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/) license.


---


## 🤝 Contributions and Collaboration

Contributions to this documentation, site, or project structure — whether via pull requests, edits, or issue discussions —  
are deeply appreciated and credited when integrated.

By contributing, you agree that your input may become part of the evolving `KIMU` project  
and may be reused in future formats, always respecting your authorship and intent.

All contributions are credited where appropriate, and used in line with the spirit of open collaboration and shared growth.

> Thank you for being part of this vision.


---


## 🏷️ Trademarks and Naming

**"KIMU"** and **"UnicòVerso"** are names associated with the original author.  
Use of these names in modified or derivative works requires prior written permission.  
Unauthorized use may constitute a violation of moral rights and trademark protection.

This is not meant to limit creative forks, but to protect the identity of the original project and its ecosystem.


